- "sought-after data treasures" refers to the data points with the highest access count and average quality score;
- "popularity" refers to the access count of each data point;
- "average quality of the data" refers to the average quality score of each data point.

High-quality data refers to data with a quality score greater than 0.7; 
The 'trend analysis' is a type of analysis; 
The 'latest' result refers to the result with the most recent analysis date.
